    "text": "ABUJA (Reuters) - Nigeria’s government has extended the search for 110 schoolgirls abducted last month to neighboring countries, the information ministry said on Friday.\nThe girls were taken from their school in the town of Dapchi, in the northeastern state of Yobe, by suspected Boko Haram militants on Feb. 19. Yobe state directly borders Niger and is also close to Nigeria’s borders with Chad and Cameroon.\nReporting by Felix Onuah; Writing by Alexis Akwagyiram; Editing by Nick Tattersall\n ",
